Step 1: Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio
• From the Balance Sheet, the debt (total liabilities) is given by Total Current Liabilities = 967271.87.
• Owner's Equity is given as Total Owner's Equity = 13963263.19.
• Debt to Equity Ratio = 967271.87 / 13963263.19 ≈ 0.0693, which rounds to 0.07.

Step 2: Calculate Net Profit Margin
• From the Income Statement, Net Profit = 963263.19 and Total Revenue = 3025437.82.
• Net Profit Margin = (963263.19 / 3025437.82) × 100 ≈ 31.80%.

Step 3: Calculate Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio
• From the Cash Flow Statement, the Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 116257.19.
• Using Total Current Liabilities = 967271.87.
• Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio = 116257.19 / 967271.87 ≈ 0.12.

Thus, the solution is presented below.

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.07",
    "Net Profit Margin": "31.80%",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "0.12"
  }
}
